    <p>Today, as promised, I'll tell you about my misadventure trying to get to the car rental place in Auckland by bus. When I left the hostel in the morning and headed toward the bus stop, I discovered there wasn't actually a stop there. I then walked down the street in the direction of travel, hoping to reach the next stop before the bus. Unfortunately, my hope was in vain - the bus zoomed past when I was just 50 meters away from the stop.</p>
    <p>I then decided to walk to the next major street and catch a different bus heading south, planning to take a taxi from there. This didn't turn out to be so simple either. The bus itself wasn't the problem this time. After arriving at the highway entrance, I called the Auckland taxi center and ordered a taxi. The person on the other end told me it would take at least 30 minutes for a taxi to arrive. Great.</p>
    <p>So there I was, standing by the roadside near the highway entrance, waiting for my taxi. And waiting. And waiting. After some time, a tall, friendly-looking young woman with freckles approached me, sipping a coffee, and asked if I was hitchhiking since I'd been waiting there so long. I explained my predicament, and before I knew it, I was sitting in the passenger seat of her car. She drove me directly to the car rental place. On the way there, we chatted about Ireland and the band Mumford &amp; Sons, which we both love.</p>
