    <p>After she dropped me off right in front of the Wendekreisen car rental office in Auckland, I went inside only to discover that the lady there had no booking under my last name. She also didn't have a booking under Sebastian. I started to sweat. I nervously fumbled for my booking confirmation from my suitcase and hoped for the best. After all, I'd already paid almost $1,000 in full. After checking her computer, it became clear that the booking was fine - the names had just been mixed up. She couldn't find the paper booking because it was under "Sebastien" rather than my last name. After that, everything was quite straightforward. All the necessary paperwork was quickly completed, and the vehicle was already prepared for departure.</p>
    <p>Next stop: Rotorua. But more about that next time.</p>
